Making a raid run smoothly often depends on how well we all buff.<br>
When on a raid, asses what buffs you will need to do your job as well as possible.<br>
Then figure out who is casting which of the buffs you need.<br>
Give them a /tell or if grouped with them, ask them in group.<br>
Once buffed, keep track of your buffs to insure that when they drop, you can ask for them again promptly.<br>
<br>
In general, here is how you should look at buffs and how important each type is:<br>
<br>
General:<br>
HP buffs are the most important buffs you can get.  These are the ones you need to be most aware of as the make the most difference to living or dying.<br>
Resist buffs are second as they can mean less damage is taken when they are needed.<br>
<br>
Melee:<br>
Again, HP buffs are the most important.<br>
Speed, this is the second most important thing for a melee as damage output relies on having this buff.<br>
Resists are more important for melee then any others as you will be standing next to the critter the whole time.<br>
AC buffs are important mostly to the Main Tank and Secondary Tank, others should not be getting hit as much, so are not as needed.<br>
Stat buffs are the least important, besides STA which gives HP, as they have, in general the least effect.<br>
<br>
Casters:<br>
HP, so you can live.<br>
Mana regen.<br>
Resists.<br>
<br>
Pay attention when special encounters require certain buffs, you will need to be sure to get these.<br>
<br>
General buffing ideas:<br>
Make sure you make a habit of placing your insta-click item buff in your top slot at all times.  This way you will not need to remove a buff to do this later.<br>
Ask for buffs in reverse order of importance, so that stat buffs are before AC, HP and so on.  This ensures that your buffs will do their job for as long as possible.  Melee should generally get haste last in a fight with a dispelling Mob.<br>
If you are aware of what buffs you need to do your job, and make sure you are buffed when needed, it will make raids go faster and smoother.<br>
Before asking for buffs, also gage what lvl of buffs you really need.<br>
For example you want Aego as your HP buff from the cleric, but the Aego clerics are sullen and completely out of mana.  If you will not be tanking during the fight, a combination of lesser cleric buffs from the FM cleric who does not have Aego yet, will probably do just as well, and speed up the buffing.<br>
<br>
Just something to keep in mind for raid buffing.<br>
