<br>
HP buffs = Focus of Spirit (60 Shaman)<br>
               Talisman of something or another (Non 60 Shaman)<br>
               Brells Mountainous Barrier (60 paladin)<br>
               Strength of Nature (51 ? + Ranger)<br>
               Symbol of something or another (Non 60 Cleric)<br>
               Riotous Health (Shaman)<br>
                <br>
Note that Strength of Nature does not stick with Brells Mountainous Barrier or other Palading Divine strength/Divine Glory spells.<br>
  <br>
AC Buffs = Aegolism (60 cleric)<br>
               Heroism/Heroic Bond (just say hero, Non 60 Cleric)<br>
               Shield of Words (Non 60 Cleric)<br>
               Call of Earth (51 ? + Ranger)<br>
               Speed of the Shissar (any Enchanter with epic)<br>
               Deleriously Nimble (Shaman)<br>
<br>
ATK buffs = Call of the Predator (60 ranger)<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
What I usually do, as a non tanking melee, First I ask for aego, but if theres only 1 60 cleric there or none, then I just settle for Symbol/hero/sow. The combination of all 3 is just about as good as aego. <br>
<br>
Next, I ask for focus if there is a 60 shm there. If none is there, ask for talisman from any other shaman. I then ask for riotous health (sta) and Deleriously Nimble (agi) from any non 60 shaman. This is courtesy so the 60 shaman isnt stuck doing all 3 buffs. <br>
<br>
Then I buff myself with Call of earth and strength of nature. but if a 60 paladin is present, I get DS or BMB from him. It doesnt stack with Strenth of Nature.<br>
<br>
If an epic enchanter is present, I ask for speed of the shissar (snake as it is commonly known as). This is not only an ac buff, but it is nice haste that is mana free...enchanter right clicks his epic =)<br>
<br>
Lastly, I call of Predator myself/group. Since this guild has a number of 60 rangers, this buff is quite easy to get and it doesnt cost much mana at all.                <br>
<br>
There are other buffs out there, like druid PoTG and other stuff. This is by far not a complete list of all buffs available from guildies, but more of a guide to go on if you dont know names/effects/levels/classes. <p><br><center>Dmourning Perkele, 60 Ranger</center><br>
